      }}>{`http://www.google.com/recaptcha`}</a>{` and create a new one. I suggest you to not check the check box of "Enable this key on all domains" to be able to debug with localhost. So, after this step, you will have a private and public key that will be required to use the ReCaptcha service.`}</p>
    <p>{`The second step is to have library to access ReCaptcha. Inside your project, add the two following NuGet Package. One is the Recaptcha API service and the other one will give you `}<strong parentName="p">{`Html helper`}</strong>{`. `}<span parentName="p" {...{
